Arms.name: Barbell Curl
Arms.description: Use a weighted Barbell to curl with both arms

Back.name: Lat Pull Down
Back.description: Pull bar to chin level. Do not overexert and bend at the waist.

Back.name: Deadlift
Back.description: Keep feet shoulder width apart. Keep Movement as vertical as possible as you lift with your lower back.

Back.name: Barbell Row
Back.description: The Bent Over Row is an exercise that tones and strengthens the lattissimus dorsi, the largest muscle in your back

Chest.name: Bench Press
Chest.description: Press with chest. Bring bar down to your chest and push straight up.

Chest.name: Flys
Chest.description: Use either cables or dumbbells. Hold weights above your chest and let them slowly fall away from your body. Clench chest as your bring them back together.

Chest.name: Push-Ups
Chest.description: Get in Push Up position. Commence push ups.

Chest.name: Incline Bench Press
Chest.description: Same thing as bench press, except on an incline.

Shoulder.name: Military Press
Shoulder.description: Similar to shoulder press but with a straight bar instead of dumbbells.

Shoulder.name: Cable Front Raise
Shoulder.description: Using a cable and both hands raise the weight directly in front of you. Do not bend your elbows.

Shoulder.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
Shoulder.description: Similar to cable front raises. Instead use a dumbbell in both hands and slowly lift as if you're trying to fly like a bird.

Legs.name: Squats
Legs.description: Place bar securely above lats but below neck. Squat down slowly as shown in video.

Legs.name: Leg Press
Legs.description: Use machine, and follow instructions in video.

Legs.name: Leg Extension
Legs.description: Use machine to extend legs. Do not overload with too much weight. Too much weight could cause injury.

Legs.name: Lunges
Legs.description: Take step forward and let standing knee almost touch the ground. Stand back up and repeat with other leg.
